protein.specific_function: Myosins are actin-based motor molecules with ATPase activity. Unconventional myosins serve in intracellular movements. Regulates Rho activity in neurons, has a role in the regulation of neuronal morphology and function

hydrolase activity, acting on acid anhydrides, in phosphorus-containing anhydrides
